using UnityEngine;

public class Character
{
    public string name;
    public int health;

    public Character(string n, int h)
    {
        name = n;
        health = h;
    }
}

public class Warrior : Character
{
    // Forgot to call base constructor!
    public Warrior(string n) 
    {
        name = n;
        health = 120;
    }
}

phase2.explanation:
When a base class has a constructor with parameters, you must call it from the derived class.

**The fix:**
```csharp
public Warrior(string n) : base(n, 120)  // ← Call base constructor
{
    // Additional setup for Warrior
}
```

**Sharp-chan says:**
"If the base class has a constructor with parameters, you must call it. It's required."
